  "body": "Similar to https://github.com/skynetservices/skydns/issues/124?\r\n\r\nAfter the NOTIFY events are send, which have REFUSED (unexpected afaik) and NOTAUTH (expected) as rcodes I get a bunch of i/o timeouts in the form of:\r\n```\r\n2016/11/09 11:20:29 [ERROR] read udp 10.0.1.91:54897->0.0.0.0:53: i/o timeout\r\n2016/11/09 11:20:29 [ERROR] read udp 10.0.1.91:56370->0.0.0.0:53: i/o timeout\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome additional info:\r\nI have 6 transfer to statements. 3 for one provider, 2 for another and 1 for AXFR being open from all IPs (firewall prevents abuse for now).\r\n\r\nThe 3 IPs from provider A are not notified and no i/o timeouts occur on these IPs.\r\nThe 2 IPs from provider B are not notified and i/o timeouts occur on these IPs.\r\n\r\n",
